 modern life. Davies shows that the science of happiness is less a science than an extension of hyper-capitalism"--cProvided by publisher.  a8 43 0aWell-beingxSocial aspects. 0aWell-beingxSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 0aWell-beingxPolitical aspects. 0aWell-beingxEconomic aspects. 0aHappinessxSocial aspects. 0aNeoliberalismxSocial aspects. 0aCapitalismxSocial aspects. 0aMarketingxSocial aspects. 0aSocial psychology. 0aEconomicsxPsychological aspects.  aHN 25 D35 2015wLCc1i34917001375489d1/11/2017e12/8/2016lON_SHELFmKEYANOn11p$18.87q1rYsYtBOOKu3/9/2015o.STAFF. Rec'd May/15 MW  aHN 25 D35 2015wLCc1i0162034825479d11/23/2016e11/23/2016kRESERVESlON_SHELFmUAHSSn4p$150.00rYsYtSHORT_LOANu8/6/2015zCOUTTS_ADD01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/nb2010020899bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/131617643